Package clientSide.gui

Class VisitReportController

  • java.lang.Object
    • common.controllers.AbstractScreen
      • clientSide.gui.VisitReportController
  • public class VisitReportController
extends AbstractScreen
    Controller for the Visit Report screen. This class manages the user interaction and data visualization for visitation patterns within a park, displaying group and individual visitor data on a scatter chart.

      • populateChart

        public void populateChart​(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.util.List<javafx.scene.chart.XYChart.Data<java.lang.Number,​java.lang.Number>>> chartData)
        Populates a scatter chart with data for group visits and individual visits. The method expects a map where keys are strings representing the type of visit ("Group" or "Individual Visitor") and values are lists of XYChart.Data objects, with each object representing a data point for the chart.
        Parameters:
        chartData - A map containing the data to be displayed on the chart. The keys should be "Group" and "Individual Visitor", and the values should be lists of XYChart.Data objects.
